  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give Sight to Children in Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Childhood blindness brings a lifetime of costs for care and dependency through a lack of employment opportunities. Uncorrected refractive error eg.myopia also prevents children from learning meaningfully, especially in rural schools where blackboards are the main tool for teaching. Half of childhood blindness can be avoided if the conditions were detected and treated early. This program aims to increase access to children&apos;s eye services in Vietnam so that children can reach their full potential.</narrative>
  </description>
